%I A176762 #9 Jul 09 2026 00:02:12
%S A176762 1,10,13,23,19,7,356,4,2,11,15,5,3,14,45,36,6,112,269,15999
%N A176762 Smallest positive integer that takes n steps to reach a cycle under iteration of the sum-of-squares-of-digits map A003132.
%C A176762 The sum-of-squares-of-digits map A003132 has two fixed points, 0 and 1, and only one cycle of length 8 which is (4 16 37 58 89 145 42 20), cf. A080709. So, "cycle" in the definition means "1 or a term of A080709". - _M. F. Hasler_, Jul 04 2026
%F A176762 a(n) = minimum of either A001273(n) or A094406(n).
%t A176762 f[n_] := Plus @@ (IntegerDigits[n]^2); t = Table[0, {25}]; k = 1; While[k < 150000001, a = Length@ NestWhileList[f, k, UnsameQ@## &, All] - 1; If[a < 25 && t[[a]] == 0, t[[a]] = k; Print[{a, k}]]; k++ ]
%Y A176762 Cf. A001273 (least happy number of height n), A003132 (sum of squares of digits), A094406 (least unhappy number to reach a cycle in n steps), A045646, A003001.
%K A176762 nonn,base,changed
%O A176762 0,2
%A A176762 _Robert G. Wilson v_, Apr 25 2010
%E A176762 Name edited by _M. F. Hasler_, Jul 04 2026
